title: Jesse Ventura - Ballotpedia
snippet: Jesse Ventura was the Governor of Minnesota. Ventura assumed office on January 8, 1999. Ventura left office on January 6, 2003. Ventura (Green Party of Alaska, Unaffiliated) ran for election for President of the United States.

title: Jesse Ventura says he’s ‘testing the waters’ for Green Party bid for president
snippet: Jesse Ventura, who served as Minnesota governor as a member of the Reform Party, said Monday that he is “testing the waters” for a potential 2020 run for president on the Green Party ticket.
